h3. Expected Behavior
Be able to import repositories from GitHub on JIRA using username/password authentication for GitHub accounts with or without two-factor authentication.
 
h3. Actual Behavior
If the GitHub account has two-factor authentication configured, no repositories will be displayed after passing authentication (inputting username, password and, subsequently, verifiaction code) on JIRA's *External System Import*.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to *Administration* > *System* > *External System Import*;
# Choose *GitHub*;
# Select *Github.com* account;
# Type in the username and password;
# Hit *Next*;
# Type in the *Authentication Code*;
# Hit *Next*;
# Notice that no repositories will appear on the screen (see screenshot);
!Screenshot 2015-05-13 15.53.52.jpg|thumbnail!

h3. Workaround
Generate a [Personal Access Token|https://help.github.com/articles/creating-an-access-token-for-command-line-use/] on GitHub and use that for authentication.

